div.p:
'Tis manifeſt that every Man has a Power to do that which God has made him able to do; and God does not require more of any Man. If there be a willing Mind, ſaith the Scripture, it is accepted according to what a Man hath, and not according to what he hath not, 2 Cor. 8.12.

He that improved his two Talents was kindly accepted, as well as he that did improve his five Talents; ſee Mat. 25. Be ſure to make the beſt Uſe that thou canſt of the Powers that thou haſt; and then if thy preſent Powers are not ſufficient to enable thee to make thy own Calling and Election ſure, God will not ſail at laſt to give thee that Power that is ſufficient: for he has made a Promiſe unto Men by the Mouth of our Bleſſed Lord, that more Grace ſhall be given to them that make a good Uſe of the Grace they have; 
                     Ʋnto every one that hath ſhall be given, ſaith he, and he ſhall have abundance; but from him that hath not, ſhall be taken away even that which he hath: See Mat. 25.29.
